That depends.  As it happens I've seen gamepads set up where the player doesn't touch the mouse and only uses the keyboard for chatting.  cursor and character movement is done by mapping mouse and keyboard commands to controls on the game pad.
<br />

<br />
I seriously doubt that substituting a gamepad for your mouse is going to qualify as something you are not allowed to do.
<br />

<br />
Even many of the hotkeys are keys to buttons on the gamepad so that the player can forage, toggle auto attack, taunt, kick, use macro'd group comments, etc without the keyboard.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=852643" target="_blank" class="postlink">Dharisk</a>
